51.1	Brain-computer_interface	Brain–computer interface	A brain–computer interface , often called a mind-machine interface (MMI), or sometimes called a direct neural interface or a brain–machine interface (BMI), is a direct communication pathway between the brain and an external device. BCIs are often directed at assisting, augmenting, or repairing human cognitive or sensory-motor functions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/54/MouseBCI.jpg
